<TITLE> Under-19 cricketers lose to Sri Lankan counterparts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 14 (bdnews24.com)  Hosts Bangladesh Under-19 team Friday lost to Sri Lankan counterparts by 14 runs in the second one-dayer at Shaheed Chandu Stadium in Bogra. The five-match series now level at 1-1 after Bangladesh handed a 13-run defeat to the visitors in the opener Wednesday. Despite a blazing 90-run knock from Marshal Ayub, the home side were 14 runs short of collapsing at 151 all out in 48.4 overs after Sri Lanka made 165 all out in 48.5 overs. Fernando (4/20) and Pathirana (4/25) shared eight wickets to rattle the Bangladesh innings. Rubel Hossain (20), Mahmudul Hasan (13) and Ashraful Aziz (12) were other notable scorers for Bangladesh, but their efforts were not enough to reach home. Earlier, Rubel (3/21), Mahmudul (3/41) and Nasir (2/37) justified their captain Suhrawardi Shuvo's decision to bowl first with restricting the visitors to 165. Thirihanna top-scored with 47 followed by Silva on 42 and Janith on 38. The third match is billed for Saturday at the same venue. 
